	<h2>Understanding PNG vs JPG</h2>
	<p><strong>PNG (Portable Network Graphics)</strong> is a lossless format that supports transparency and is ideal for graphics, logos, and images with text. However, PNG files are typically larger in size.</p>
	<p><strong>JPG/JPEG (Joint Photographic Experts Group)</strong> uses lossy compression to create much smaller files, making it perfect for photographs and images where transparency isn't needed. JPG files don't support transparency, so transparent areas will be converted to a solid color (typically white).</p>
	<p><strong>When to convert:</strong> Use this converter when you need smaller file sizes for web use, email attachments, or when uploading to platforms that don't support PNG. Perfect for photographs, background images, and any image where transparency isn't required.</p>
